Bandits were said to have killed a staff member of Toto Local Government Area of Nasarawa State, Mohammad Shuaibu and abducted his wife. A resident, Abdullahi Ahmed, said the abductors were demanding N2m. People identified as Basaru Rukaiya, Aishat Zakari, Chinedu Ide, Reuben Ibrahim and Vivian Ibrahim, all of whom are from Yelwa village of Toto Local Government, were also said to have been abducted Saturday night. One Alhaji Mohammad Shuaibu was also said to have been abducted at Unguwan Bai part of the local government area. Police Commissioner in the state Mr Bola Longe said he was informed about only two cases, saying the command was investigating them.  Nasarawa: Kidnappers kill council staff, kidnap his wife 7 abducted in Birnin Gwari in 1 week Bandits abduct 7 in Birnin-Gwari Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin